                              THE AMERICA LICENSE - Version 2.0
                         Edition the the First, Sovereign and August  
           Proclaimed upon this Twenty‑First Day of April, in the Year of Our Lord Two Thousand and Twenty‑Five  

BE it known and manifest unto all persons both gentle and humble, that in the enduring spirit of liberty and enterprise, and to uphold the grand ideals of uninhibited exchange of knowledge and creation, the licensor hereby doth promulgate and ordain this venerable charter, to be henceforth denominated “The America License,” wherein shall be enshrined the rights, duties, and noble exhortations by which any recipient—hereinafter called “Thou” or “Thee”—may partake freely and righteously of the Software and its appendages.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
I.  PREAMBLE AND RECITALS  
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
Whereas the Creator, impelled by a love of advancement and fellowship, hath devised this wondrous Software, together with all documentation, exempla, and illustrative adjuncts (collectively “The Software”), and  
Whereas the Creator doth verily affirm that the dissemination of knowledge and the unbarred circulation of intellectual endeavour are the lifeblood of progress, and  
Whereas it is meet and proper to entreat each possessor of The Software to observe the conditions herein contained, that a commonwealth of minds may flourish in harmony and innovation;  

Now, therefore, the Creator doth, in witness whereof and for the encouragement of all free artisans of the digital realm, grant this License under the solemn terms following.  

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
II.  DEFINITIONS  
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
2.1  “The Software” shall signify the original corpus of code and all allied files, even to the minutest exemplar and the most modest auxiliary script.  
2.2  “The Licensor” shall denote the party or parties who hold rightful claim and authorship over The Software.  
2.3  “The Licensee,” “Thou,” or “Thee” shall denote any natural person, partnership, corporation, or other entity which accepts this License’s blessings.  
2.4  “Derivative Works” shall include every modification, translation, augmentation, or reengineering of The Software, whether presented in altered or enhanced guise.  

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
III.  GRANT OF RIGHTS  
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
3.1  Subject to the observance of the Covenants and Conditions herein set forth, the Licensor doth grant unto Thee a perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, royalty‑free, non‑exclusive licence to:  
   (a)  employ and execute The Software for any lawful enterprise or whimsical fancy;  
   (b)  reproduce, publish, and distribute the Software, in whole or in part, verbatim or in transmuted form;  
   (c)  prepare and promulgate Derivative Works thereof;  
   (d)  vend, lease, or otherwise transfer copies of The Software or its Derivative Works;  
   (e)  grant sublicences to others, that the flame of sharing may be carried forth to distant shores and future ages.  

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
IV.  OBLIGATIONS AND CONDITIONS  
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
4.1  In the spirit of mutual trust and transparent governance, any redistribution, whether of the Software untouched or of a transformed derivative, shall be accompanied by:  
   (i)    a reproduction of the original Copyright Notice;  
   (ii)   the full and unabridged text of this License;  
   (iii)  a clear and conspicuous account of any alterations, augmentations, or improvements made upon The Software.  

4.2  Should Thee wish to bestow The Software as part of a larger assemblage or collective work, the foregoing obligations shall apply to the portion so derived, provided that a reasonable mechanism exists by which recipients may procure the unaltered source.  

4.3  The Licensor doth entreat Thee, in good faith and fair dealing, to credit the original authors and contributors upon reasonable occurrence, whether in documentation, an attribution file, or a digital splash screen.  

4.4  This License shall not restrict Thee from exercising any right or remedy otherwise conferred by law, nor shall it impose burdens beyond those herein expressly articulated.  

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
V.  MORAL EXHORTATION AND PATRIOTIC ORATION  
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
5.1  Let it be declared, by public voice and private resolve, that the liberality thus extended is founded upon the highest ideals of fraternity, progress, and the unalienable liberties of mind and spirit.  
5.2  May each steward of The Software bear in heart and mind the edict that collaboration is virtue, that generosity begets innovation, and that through unity of purpose the digital commons may endure without impediment.  
5.3  In commemoration of these exalted tenets, let Thee raise the standard of open sharing as a beacon to all who yearn for discovery, invention, and the noble exercise of creative freedom.  

